Package: btf
Type: Package
Title: Estimates univariate function with domain [0,1] via Bayesian trend
    filtering
Version: 1.0
Date: 2014-07-14
Author: Edward A. Roualdes
Maintainer: Edward A. Roualdes <edward.roualdes@uky.edu>
Description: Trend filtering \link[genlasso]{trendfilter} uses the generalized
    lasso \pkg{genlasso} framework to fit an adaptive polynomial of degree k to
    estimate the function f_0 at each input x_i in the model: \deqn{y_i =
    f_0(x_i) + \epsilon_i} \eqn{i = 1, \ldots, n, \epsilon_i}, \eqn{\epsilon_i}
    is sub-Gaussian with E(\epsilon_i) = 0.  Bayesian trend filtering adapts
    the genlasso framework to a fully Bayesian hierarchical model, estimating
    the penalty parameter \eqn{\lambda} within a tractable Gibbs sampler.
License: GPL (>= 2.0)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 0.11.0),
    RcppEigen (>= 0.3.2.1.1),
    Matrix,
    coda,
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppEigen
NeedsCompilation: yes
